{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:55:10.050Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing State & Effects**\n\nI'm now integrating state variables and a `useEffect` hook into `ClientWorkspace.tsx`. The goal is to simulate fluctuating CPU levels for Singapore, London, and New York, alongside associated system data points. This initial setup focuses on basic functionality.\n\n\n**Refining the Scanning Flow**\n\nI'm now focusing on the authentication flow, specifically refining how the `scanStep` state increments within the `handleAuth` function. The next step is to dynamically display the animated holographic scanning element when `scanning` is active, enhancing user feedback during the process. I'm aiming for a seamless integration.\n\n\n**Simulating Hardware Handshake**\n\nI've replaced the simple `setTimeout` with a simulated handshake sequence. Now, the `handleAuth` function increments `scanStep` through a series of messages to improve the illusion. This includes simulating hardware security module scans and signature verifications. Next, I'll integrate the holographic scanning UI based on `scanning` and `scanStep`.\n\n\n**Implementing Data Fluctuation**\n\nI've implemented CPU level fluctuations for Singapore, London, and New York within the `useEffect` hook. I'm using state variables for each city and a separate state for data points. The CPU levels and data points are updated at 1.5-second intervals, using random deltas within specified boundaries. This generates dynamic system data updates.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:55:10.059Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"zazkkjc5","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/portal/ClientWorkspace.tsx","old_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState } from \"react\";\nimport Link from \"next/link\";\nimport { \n  Lock, Shield, Key, CheckCircle, RefreshCw, Layers, FileText, \n  CreditCard, CheckSquare, MessageSquare, BarChart3, ShieldCheck, \n  Cpu, ArrowRight, UserCheck, AlertCircle, HelpCircle, Download \n} from \"lucide-react\";\n\nexport default function ClientWorkspace() {\n  const [authed, setAuthed] = useState(false);\n  const [scanning, setScanning] = useState(false);\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(\"dashboard\");\n\n  // Mock support ticket state\n  const [tickets, setTickets] = useState([\n    { id: \"T-882\", subject: \"London core replication delay\", status: \"Investigating\" }\n  ]);\n  const [newSubject, setNewSubject] = useState(\"\");\n\n  // Simulated authentication handler\n  const handleAuth = async () => {\n    setScanning(true);\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1200));\n    setScanning(false);\n    setAuthed(true);\n  };","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport Link from \"next/link\";\nimport { \n  Lock, Shield, Key, CheckCircle, RefreshCw, Layers, FileText, \n  CreditCard, CheckSquare, MessageSquare, BarChart3, ShieldCheck, \n  Cpu, ArrowRight, UserCheck, AlertCircle, HelpCircle, Download, Activity\n} from \"lucide-react\";\n\nexport default function ClientWorkspace() {\n  const [authed, setAuthed] = useState(false);\n  const [scanning, setScanning] = useState(false);\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(\"dashboard\");\n  \n  // Scanning micro-interaction states\n  const [scanStep, setScanStep] = useState(0);\n  const scanMessages = [\n    \"Establishing zero-trust handshake...\",\n    \"Scanning hardware security module...\",\n    \"Verifying passkey signature (SHA-256)...\",\n    \"Decapsulating session enclave...\"\n  ];\n\n  // Fluctuating metric states for telemetry\n  const [cpuSingapore, setCpuSingapore] = useState(42);\n  const [cpuLondon, setCpuLondon] = useState(18);\n  const [cpuNY, setCpuNY] = useState(89);\n  const [dataPoints, setDataPoints] = useState([35, 42, 38, 48, 52, 45, 58, 62, 59, 64]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!authed) return;\n    const interval = setInterval(() => {\n      setCpuSingapore(prev => {\n        const delta = Math.floor(Math.random() * 7) - 3;\n        return Math.min(100, Math.max(10, prev + delta));\n      });\n      setCpuLondon(prev => {\n        const delta = Math.floor(Math.random() * 5) - 2;\n        return Math.min(100, Math.max(10, prev + delta));\n      });\n      setCpuNY(prev => {\n        const delta = Math.floor(Math.random() * 9) - 4;\n        return Math.min(100, Math.max(10, prev + delta));\n      });\n      setDataPoints(prev => {\n        const nextVal = Math.min(100, Math.max(20, prev[prev.length - 1] + (Math.floor(Math.random() * 14) - 7)));\n        return [...prev.slice(1), nextVal];\n      });\n    }, 1500);\n    return () => clearInterval(interval);\n  }, [authed]);\n\n  // Mock support ticket state\n  const [tickets, setTickets] = useState([\n    { id: \"T-882\", subject: \"London core replication delay\", status: \"Investigating\" }\n  ]);\n  const [newSubject, setNewSubject] = useState(\"\");\n\n  // Simulated authentication handler\n  const handleAuth = async () => {\n    setScanning(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    const interval = setInterval(() => {\n      setScanStep(prev => {\n        if (prev < 3) return prev + 1;\n        return prev;\n      });\n    }, 450);\n\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1800));\n    clearInterval(interval);\n    setScanning(false);\n    setAuthed(true);\n  };"}}}
