{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:56:16.389Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"21utt7f7","input":{"summary":"Successfully polished and enhanced the 'Contact Portal Client Control Center' pages to achieve an elite, ultra-premium, 2026-grade design.\n\nKey additions & improvements:\n1. **Interactive SVG Agent Topology Map (Control Center)**: In the 'Agent Health Monitor' tab of the Control Center workspace, replaced the static diagnostic thread log box with an interactive SVG topology node network representing GFF's main enclaves (Retail, Ore-Mesh, and Governance Core). Clicking on any node dynamically filters and populates a side telemetry panel with real-time reactive loads, enclave memory checks, hash credentials, and live-simulated log outputs.\n2. **Futuristic Holographic Biometric scan (Client Portal SSO)**: Enhanced the single-sign-on Zero-Trust SSO login gate in the Client Workspace with an advanced, interactive holographic grid scanning sequence. Triggering passkey verification starts a live, step-by-step progress logging check (enclave handshakes, HSM scans, passkey signatures) overlaid with animated grid crosshairs and pulsating targets.\n3. **Live Fluctuating SVG Telemetry Sparklines (Analytics)**: Added an elite live compute telemetry sparkline graph within the Analytics tab of the Client Workspace. Features fluctuating, real-time workload statistics mapped across three global cores (Singapore, London, New York) with a reactive SVG path line and pulsing indicator dots that morph and render smoothly every 1.5 seconds.\n4. **Coherence & Standards compliance**: Retained the secure local simulated sandboxing (frontend-only) to avoid any real backends/auth, maintained the dark neon-accented premium aesthetic, ensured complete mobile responsiveness, and verified perfect TypeScript static type checking.","verified":true}}}
